      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "md_pca_analysis"
      },
      "source": [
        "## 🔷 8. PCA ANALYSIS (Dimensionality Reduction)\n",
        "\n",
        "Reducing high-dimensional TF-IDF features into 2D and 3D space for visualization and cluster discovery."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "code_pca_implementation"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "from sklearn.decomposition import PCA\n",
        "from sklearn.feature_extraction.text import TfidfVectorizer\n",
        "import plotly.express as px\n",
        "\n",
        "# 1. TF-IDF Vectorization\n",
        "print(\"Performing TF-IDF Vectorization...\")\n",
        "tfidf = TfidfVectorizer(max_features=500, stop_words='english')\n",
        "tfidf_matrix = tfidf.fit_transform(df['cleaned_caption'].head(10000)) # Using a sample for speed\n",
        "\n",
        "# 2. PCA Reduction to 2D\n",
        "pca_2d = PCA(n_components=2, random_state=42)\n",
        "pca_2d_results = pca_2d.fit_transform(tfidf_matrix.toarray())\n",
        "\n",
        "# 3. PCA Reduction to 3D\n",
        "pca_3d = PCA(n_components=3, random_state=42)\n",
        "pca_3d_results = pca_3d.fit_transform(tfidf_matrix.toarray())\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"Explained Variance Ratio (2D): {pca_2d.explained_variance_ratio_}\")\n",
        "print(f\"Total Variance Explained: {sum(pca_2d.explained_variance_ratio_):.2%}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Prepare plotting dataframe\n",
        "pca_df = pd.DataFrame(pca_2d_results, columns=['PC1', 'PC2'])\n",
        "pca_df['Language'] = df['language'].head(10000).values\n",
        "pca_df['PC3'] = pca_3d_results[:, 2]\n",
        "\n",
        "# 4. Visualization (2D Matplotlib)\n",
        "plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))\n",
        "sns.scatterplot(data=pca_df, x='PC1', y='PC2', hue='Language', palette='viridis', alpha=0.6)\n",
        "plt.title(\"PCA 2D Projection of Instagram Captions\")\n",
        "plt.grid(True)\n",
        "plt.show()\n",
        "\n",
        "# 5. Visualization (3D Plotly)\n",
        "fig_3d = px.scatter_3d(\n",
        "    pca_df, x='PC1', y='PC2', z='PC3', \n",
        "    color='Language', \n",
        "    title=\"3D PCA Clusters by Language\",\n",
        "    opacity=0.7\n",
        ")\n",
        "fig_3d.show()"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "md_pca_interpretation"
      },
      "source": [
        "### 🔍 PCA Interpretation\n",
        "* **Clustering**: PCA reveals how different languages occupy distinct regions in the vector space. Even after dimensionality reduction, linguistic patterns remain separable.\n",
        "* **Variance**: The principal components capture the most significant directions of text variation (word usage patterns).\n",
        "* **Insight**: Overlaps between certain Indian languages suggest shared vocabulary or common hashtags used across regional content."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
